The paper proposes a machine comprehension architecture for ellipsis and coreference resolution, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper specifically focuses on resolving ellipsis and coreference, which are common challenges in NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates its models across standard benchmarks, which is a common practice in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions evaluating its models on coreference resolution, which can involve analyzing visual information, making computer vision (cs.CV) a possible sub-category as well.
